Zenon Walter Pylyshyn (; born 1937) is a Canadian cognitive scientist and philosopher.
He holds degrees in engineering-physics (B.Eng. 1959) from McGill University and in control systems (M.Sc. 1960) and experimental psychology (Ph.D. 1963), both from the Regina Campus, University of Saskatchewan. His dissertation was on the application of information theory to studies of human short-term memory. He was a Canada Council Senior fellow from 1963â€“1964.
